03:23.990 --> 03:24.630
of the patient

03:24.650 --> 03:25.820
have to be controlled

03:25.850 --> 03:26.530
by his own brain nerves.

03:28.600 --> 03:29.710
Hope everything goes well.

03:30.400 --> 03:31.600
Take it easy.

03:32.040 --> 03:33.730
-Please.
- Please.

03:35.550 --> 03:35.870
Please.

03:45.870 --> 03:47.200
Today's focus is on items two and four.

03:59.400 --> 03:59.720
Okay.

04:04.090 --> 04:05.490
Step one, motor imagery.

04:06.440 --> 04:06.770
Grandpa.

04:07.240 --> 04:08.480
Visualize in your mind

04:08.610 --> 04:09.650
which leg to take first

04:10.120 --> 04:10.760
and how to get to

04:10.760 --> 04:11.800
the edge of the table.

04:39.880 --> 04:40.490
Very good.

04:41.040 --> 04:42.610
Step two, grab action.

04:43.600 --> 04:44.040
Grandpa.

04:44.240 --> 04:46.080
Try to grab this soy milk cup.

04:52.700 --> 04:53.580
Take it easy, grandpa.

04:54.240 --> 04:55.350
Just like our usual training.

04:56.520 --> 04:57.100
Lift it up.

04:59.510 --> 04:59.870
Right.

05:02.390 --> 05:03.600
No worries.

05:05.400 --> 05:06.750
Take it easy. Slow down.

05:20.760 --> 05:21.790
No worries. Slow down.

05:44.700 --> 05:45.540
Great.

05:59.480 --> 06:00.150
Record it.

06:03.660 --> 06:04.900
I’ve had it, grandpa.

06:13.760 --> 06:14.710
Record additional actions.

06:19.680 --> 06:21.370
I have something to say.

06:22.790 --> 06:23.760
All of you can see that

06:24.400 --> 06:25.830
today's result

06:26.280 --> 06:27.070
is a success

06:27.300 --> 06:28.540
and everyone is happy about it.

06:29.440 --> 06:30.250
But

06:30.450 --> 06:31.610
I don't want to talk about that.

06:32.460 --> 06:33.300
Instead, what I want to say

06:33.330 --> 06:34.510
is the hardships in the process.

06:35.240 --> 06:36.500
This patient

06:36.710 --> 06:37.750
had completely

06:38.250 --> 06:39.460
lost his motor skills

06:39.490 --> 06:40.380
due to a stroke last year.

06:40.960 --> 06:42.040
It put a lot of pressure

06:42.040 --> 06:43.400
on him psychologically.

06:43.940 --> 06:44.540
Not to mention

06:44.790 --> 06:46.470
cooperating with the experiment,

06:46.840 --> 06:47.800
he even rejected

06:47.800 --> 06:49.080
the most basic communication

06:49.150 --> 06:50.440
with others.

06:51.060 --> 06:52.580
But as you can see today,

06:53.390 --> 06:54.120
his mood

06:54.120 --> 06:55.190
has changed dramatically

06:55.650 --> 06:56.240
since being fitted

06:56.240 --> 06:57.620
with our exoskeleton.

06:58.280 --> 06:58.880
He also had

06:58.960 --> 07:00.370
a humorous interaction

07:00.390 --> 07:01.950
with Xiao Yuhe today.

07:01.970 --> 07:02.420
Right?

07:03.650 --> 07:05.120
That’s all.

07:05.240 --> 07:06.400
Let’s invite Xiao Yuhe,

07:06.520 --> 07:07.410
the technical backbone,

07:07.520 --> 07:08.480
to introduce you

07:08.480 --> 07:09.190
the technical details.

07:09.340 --> 07:09.650
Okay?

07:10.370 --> 07:11.210
In fact,

07:11.210 --> 07:11.990
as you can see,

07:12.470 --> 07:13.930
although grandpa hasn’t fully recovered,

07:14.400 --> 07:15.960
he can control the exoskeleton

07:15.960 --> 07:17.010
to do some simple body movements

07:17.030 --> 07:18.630
through nerve signals.

07:19.040 --> 07:20.480
Drinking soy milk and eating fried dough sticks

07:20.480 --> 07:21.200
is no problem for him.

07:23.290 --> 07:24.770
For paralyzed patients,

07:24.800 --> 07:25.520
this is something

07:25.520 --> 07:26.990
that is unimaginable.

07:27.720 --> 07:28.820
Senior Xiao is so great.

07:33.340 --> 07:34.300
Alright.

07:36.010 --> 07:36.530
Your turn.

07:37.250 --> 07:38.360
The biggest technical difficulty

07:38.360 --> 07:39.659
we encountered in this project

07:39.760 --> 07:41.400
was to correlate neuronal activity patterns

07:41.420 --> 07:42.760
with motor intentions

07:42.760 --> 07:44.280
to form specific trigger signals.

07:44.310 --> 07:45.070
The process of

07:45.090 --> 07:46.310
controlling the required exoskeleton

07:46.340 --> 07:47.890
according to the signal requires the patient

07:47.909 --> 07:49.470
to carry out certain training in the early stage.

07:49.710 --> 07:51.030
Yes, because of this,

07:51.060 --> 07:52.180
we continued to optimize it,

07:52.300 --> 07:53.180
and finally developed

07:53.220 --> 07:54.800
a brain-like artificial intelligence decoder.

07:55.050 --> 07:56.540
Through virtual reality training,

07:56.840 --> 07:58.080
it has achieved

07:58.120 --> 07:59.159
more accurate manipulation.

07:59.390 --> 08:00.460
That's why grandpa

08:00.480 --> 08:02.010
can operate so freely today.

08:02.220 --> 08:02.570
Right.

08:02.710 --> 08:05.150
At present, the number of paralyzed people

08:05.190 --> 08:06.370
caused by stroke,

08:06.400 --> 08:07.810
brain and spinal cord injury in the world

08:07.840 --> 08:09.880
has reached nearly 100 million people.

08:09.880 --> 08:10.490
There are 20 to 30 million

08:10.520 --> 08:11.360
in our country,

08:11.400 --> 08:13.520
and the data is still rising.

08:13.680 --> 08:14.330
In the future,

08:14.360 --> 08:15.730
our system and equipment

08:15.760 --> 08:16.400
will be further

08:16.400 --> 08:18.070
iterated and updated

08:18.120 --> 08:19.210
to solve more

08:19.230 --> 08:20.160
clinical problems,

08:20.440 --> 08:21.370
help patients

08:21.390 --> 08:23.190
rebuild their behavioral

08:23.280 --> 08:24.400
and language functions,

08:24.560 --> 08:26.040
and improve their quality of life.

08:26.120 --> 08:28.120
As an extension of human senses,

08:28.460 --> 08:29.170
the value of science

08:29.560 --> 08:30.720
is to give those who need it

08:30.740 --> 08:31.460
a promise that

08:31.590 --> 08:32.730
they can

08:32.960 --> 08:33.890
live a better life.

08:41.799 --> 08:43.559
I didn't expect our major

08:43.559 --> 08:44.159
to be so amazing.

08:44.340 --> 08:45.530
Of course.

08:46.070 --> 08:47.350
Although our major is difficult,

08:47.460 --> 08:48.870
it is of great use.

08:49.440 --> 08:50.480
That’s why Xiao

08:50.480 --> 08:51.650
is usually so strict with us.

08:52.640 --> 08:54.440
Next time I will take you

08:54.440 --> 08:55.960
to see those kids with autism.

08:56.080 --> 08:56.730
They also adopted

08:56.760 --> 08:57.600
our research and development results.

08:57.750 --> 08:58.710
Maybe by then

08:59.200 --> 09:00.620
you will understand Yuhebetter.

09:02.130 --> 09:02.920
We hope to

09:03.170 --> 09:05.200
continue to deepen

09:05.220 --> 09:06.350
research in this area

09:06.770 --> 09:07.890
and lay a solid foundation

09:09.800 --> 09:10.980
for brain-computer

09:11.010 --> 09:12.130
interface research.

